reviews.text: Nice, fresh food.

Small chàh chaān teng on busy Leighton Road. Prices are good, portions are really generous and service is friendly, quick and efficient. Ying man (English) menu is standard and staff are also conversant in English. They also have set lunch menu with main dish together with a soup and hot drink. If you order any of the curry rice dishes, you can custom the spiciness to your liking. Perfect for a quick in and out, no fuss meal

result.name: 生龍清湯腩

reviews.text:
Service aside, it offers the one of the best beef noodles in town.
Fragrant of beef is perfectly brought out by the broth and fused with the noodles. A deep fried fish skin is highly recommended to down the bowl with.
Curry is another specialty, minimum spiciness is recommended not because you can't take the heat, but that is just right with the bouquet of aroma the curry offers.
Thursday 2pm, they didn't have the clear broth brisket serving, which is part of their business name, and the reason why I went. Their "seasoned" beef brisket serving was unremarkable
Good food and service
Have lunch here with a steam fish lunch.  Delicious!!!
I come here for breakfast at times, and order the beef brisket macaroni, which I think is unique to here. Side orders are pretty standard, price is reasonable.

reviews.text: 比起最好食的牛腩差少少，中上食物水平但價錢貴過好多名店
黑白胡椒牛尾飯有特色, 非常開胃!

Curry is another specialty, minimum spiciness is recommended not because you can't take the heat, but that is just right with the bouquet of aroma the curry offers.
多年在附近會所打網球，路過都是幫趁麥奀記，或到天后幫趁大利，華姐，八寶清湯腩。因感覺茶餐廳清湯腩好極有限，但出乎以料幫襯過一次後觀感大改，牛腩及湯底不錯，價錢屬中上，至今已幫趁多次。
